The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Cong on Koda
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Cong on Koda
                            
	Nov. 26: The Congress today suggested that it was not averse to taking the support of Madhu Koda, the former Jharkhand chief minister accused of amassing wealth beyond his means, as long as he wasnt held guilty by a court and he respected the partys commitment to secular development.                                                                                                                                                          
